---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="Reach — Check your site for accessibility" description="Reach: quick checks, full reports, simple history. npx reach or npm install -g reach.">
  <article>
    <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 id="hero-heading">Reach</h1>
        <p class="hero-tagline">
          Check your site for accessibility—one page or a whole site. Quick checks, full reports, no jargon. Built for <a href="https://bun.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bun</a>.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="#get-started" class="btn btn-primary">Get started</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/softwarebyze/accessibility-auditor" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="section" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="features-heading">What you can do</h2>
        <ul class="feature-grid">
          <li>
            <h3>Quick or full check</h3>
            <p>One URL: <code>quick</code> for a fast pass/fail, <code>audit</code> for a full report—what’s wrong, how serious, and how to fix it.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Check a whole site</h3>
            <p><code>crawl</code> discovers pages and checks each one. Set a page limit and depth; export one JSON for the whole run.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>See your history</h3>
            <p>Results are stored locally. View trends with <code>reach history</code>; compare runs over time.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>MCP server</h3>
            <p>Run the MCP server so AI assistants can run checks, fetch history, or pull a result by ID.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>JSON export</h3>
            <p>Output to the console or to a JSON file—handy for CI, reports, or sharing with your team.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Honest about limits</h3>
            <p>Automated checks only catch some issues. We spell out what’s covered and suggest pairing with manual testing when it matters.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="how-it-works" class="section" aria-labelledby="how-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="how-heading">How it works</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li><strong>Open</strong> — Reach opens your page in a headless browser.</li>
          <li><strong>Check</strong> — It runs common accessibility rules (WCAG 2.1 AA) on the real page.</li>
          <li><strong>Report</strong> — You get a list of issues (critical → minor), with guidance on how to fix them, in the console or as JSON.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Because it checks the real page your users see, you’re testing what actually ships.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="get-started" class="section" aria-labelledby="get-started-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="get-started-heading">Get started</h2>
        <p>Run without installing:</p>
        <pre class="block"><code>npx reach quick https://example.com
npx reach audit https://example.com</code></pre>
        <p>Or install and use the <code>reach</code> command:</p>
        <pre class="block"><code>npm install -g reach

reach quick https://example.com
reach audit https://example.com --output json --file report.json
reach crawl https://example.com --max-pages 25
reach history</code></pre>
        <p>For the full command reference and options (<code>--verbose</code>, <code>--show-checks</code>, <code>--timeout</code>, etc.), see the <a href="https://github.com/softwarebyze/accessibility-auditor#readme">README</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section cta" aria-labelledby="cta-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="cta-heading">Ready to audit?</h2>
        <p>Run <code>npx reach audit https://yoursite.com</code> or install with <code>npm install -g reach</code>. Use crawl + JSON export and history to track progress.</p>
        <a href="https://github.com/softwarebyze/accessibility-auditor" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .hero-tagline {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 540px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }
  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1rem;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }
  .btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 2px; }
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }
  .btn-secondary {
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .section {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }
  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .feature-grid {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .feature-grid h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .feature-grid p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .steps {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .steps li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  .block {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .block code {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .cta h2 { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .cta p { color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem; }
</style>
